{"key":"post-7454606","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7454606</id>\n<content>Pan cyan mycelium is whispy and light, so is often mistaken for contaminants.  I wouldn't recommend sterilizing manure or straw.  When you get a clean culture, inoculate grains, and then when they fully colonize, spawn them into pasterurized horse manure.  Pans do best with a thin substrate, about 1 1/2&quot; thick.  Use a thin casing layer too, 1/4&quot; thick.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7454658</next>\n<prev>7454379</prev>\n<first>7454227</first>\n<last>7461079</last>\n<when>1190810306</when>\n<utime>09/26/07 03:38 PM</utime>\n</post>"}